%% KubeRay Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Controller
    participant K8sAPI as K8s API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant KubeRay as KubeRay Operator<br/>SA: kuberay-operator
    participant Dashboard as Ray Head Dashboard<br/>8265/TCP HTTP plaintext
    participant HeadPod as Ray Head Pod<br/>6379/TCP GCS
    participant WorkerPod as Ray Worker Pods
    participant ServeSvc as Serve Service<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant Client as External Client

    Note over User,Client: Flow 1: RayCluster Lifecycle

    User->>K8sAPI: Create RayCluster CR<br/>HTTPS/443 | Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>KubeRay: Watch event (RayCluster)
    KubeRay->>K8sAPI: Create Head Pod, Worker Pods<br/>Services, Ingress/Route<br/>HTTPS/443 | SA Token
    K8sAPI->>HeadPod: Schedule & start pods<br/>10250/TCP | Client cert
    WorkerPod->>HeadPod: Connect to GCS<br/>6379/TCP | plaintext

    Note over User,Client: Flow 2: RayJob Submission

    User->>K8sAPI: Create RayJob CR<br/>HTTPS/443 | Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>KubeRay: Watch event (RayJob)
    KubeRay->>K8sAPI: Create RayCluster (if needed)<br/>HTTPS/443 | SA Token
    KubeRay->>Dashboard: Submit job via REST API<br/>HTTP/8265 | plaintext | No Auth
    Dashboard-->>KubeRay: Job status response
    KubeRay->>K8sAPI: Create K8s Job (submitter)<br/>HTTPS/443 | SA Token

    Note over User,Client: Flow 3: RayService Serve Deployment

    User->>K8sAPI: Create RayService CR<br/>HTTPS/443 | Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>KubeRay: Watch event (RayService)
    KubeRay->>K8sAPI: Create RayCluster + Services<br/>HTTPS/443 | SA Token
    KubeRay->>Dashboard: Deploy Serve config<br/>HTTP/8265 | plaintext | No Auth
    Dashboard-->>KubeRay: Serve deployment status
    Client->>ServeSvc: Inference request<br/>HTTP/8000 | plaintext | No Auth
    ServeSvc-->>Client: Inference response
